<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 05 at 9:08PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Toombs
County through 945 PM EDT...
At 908 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Johnson Corner, or near
Plant Hatch. This storm was nearly stationary.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
South Thompson, English Eddy, Center, Toombs Central, Johnson Corner
and New Branch.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
